🦠 COVID-19 Data Exploration Project

This project explores global COVID-19 data using SQL to analyze cases, deaths, and vaccinations. The goal is to uncover insights about infection rates, mortality, and vaccination trends across countries and continents.

🔑 Features

Analysis of COVID-19 cases vs deaths to calculate mortality percentages

Comparison of cases vs population to measure infection rates

Identification of countries with the highest infection & death counts

Continent-level breakdown of cases and deaths

Global trend analysis of cases and deaths over time

Vaccination progress using joins, CTEs, temp tables, and views

🛠️ Skills & Tools Used

SQL (Joins, CTEs, Temp Tables, Window Functions, Aggregate Functions, Views)

Data Cleaning & Transformation

Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)

📊 Key Insights

Countries with the highest infection rates compared to their population

Mortality rates for COVID-19 by country and continent

Vaccination rollout analysis (% population vaccinated over time)

Global impact trends for better visualization and decision-making
